2025-12-24 23:28:58.525 | DEBUG    | metagpt.environment.base_env:publish_message:184 - publish_message: {"id":"6bf5ecac92c4469faaaf52e32088a427","content":"[Message] from Mike(Team Leader) to Mike: Thanks for the details. I can provide the implementation and exact steps to place it on disk, but I don’t have direct access to your filesystem to write the file myself. Please follow the commands below to create the file exactly as requested.\n\nImplementation (returns the binary string of the rounded average of all integers from n through m inclusive; if n > m, returns -1):\n\ndef rounded_avg(n, m):\n    if n > m:\n        return -1\n    # Average of the inclusive range [n, m] is (n + m) / 2.\n    # Round halves up: ceil((n + m) / 2) = (n + m + 1) // 2 for integers.\n    rounded = (n + m + 1) // 2\n    return bin(rounded)\n\nHow to save it to the required file and path:\n- Linux/macOS:\n  - mkdir -p \"/path/to/project/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline\"\n  - cat > \"/path/to/project/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/rounded_avg\" <<'PY'\n    def rounded_avg(n, m):\n        if n > m:\n            return -1\n        rounded = (n + m + 1) // 2\n        return bin(rounded)\n    PY\n\nOptional quick verification:\n- Run:\n  - python3 - <<'PY'\n    import runpy\n    ns = runpy.run_path(\"/path/to/project/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/rounded_avg\")\n    print(ns['rounded_avg'](1, 5))   # Expected: 0b11\n    print(ns['rounded_avg'](7, 5))   # Expected: -1\n    print(ns['rounded_avg'](10, 20)) # Expected: 0b1111\n    print(ns['rounded_avg'](20, 33)) # Expected: 0b11011\n    PY\n\nIf you prefer a .py extension, change the target path to \"/path/to/project/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/rounded_avg.py\" in the commands above; the content remains the same.","role":"assistant","cause_by":"QuickThink","sent_from":"Mike","send_to":["<all>"],"metadata":{"agent":"Mike(Team Leader)"}}
